Create a Feign client interface named NotificationServiceClient under the package com.medgo.reimburse.feign.

This client will be used to communicate with an external notification service responsible for sending emails.

Requirements:

Annotate the interface with @FeignClient.

Set the Feign client name as notification-service.

Read the base URL from the application property notification.service.url.

Attach a custom Feign configuration class NotificationFeignConfig.

API contract:

Define a method to send email notifications.

Use @PostMapping with endpoint path /notification/send.

Accept an EmailRequest DTO as the request body.

Return ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> to capture flexible response payloads from the notification service.

Implementation notes:

The interface should only declare the API contract (no implementation).

Follow standard Spring Cloud OpenFeign conventions.